{meta: artist Porter Wagoner}
{meta: composer Gene Wilson}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[D7]Tricks of the trade tricks of the trade
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G]Don't scorn me if I slip around on [D7]you
[G]And don't hate me if I fancy someone new
[D7]Don't blame me if my love just can't be true
[G]It's just the tricks of the trade I've learned from you
{end_of_verse}

